      • setUsernameClaim

        public ProvidersTypes.CreateSpec.Builder setUsernameClaim(java.lang.String usernameClaim)
        The claim from the upstream identity provider ID token or user info endpoint to inspect to obtain the username for the given user. This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1. If null, the upstream issuer URL will be concatenated with the 'sub' claim to generate the username to be used with Kubernetes.
        Parameters:
        usernameClaim - New value for the property.

      • setGroupsClaim

        public ProvidersTypes.CreateSpec.Builder setGroupsClaim(java.lang.String groupsClaim)
        The claim from the upstream identity provider ID token or user info endpoint to inspect to obtain the groups for the given user. This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1. If null, no groups will be used from the upstream identity provider.
        Parameters:
        groupsClaim - New value for the property.

      • setCertificateAuthorityData

        public ProvidersTypes.CreateSpec.Builder setCertificateAuthorityData(java.lang.String certificateAuthorityData)
        Certificate authority data to be used to establish HTTPS connections with the identity provider. This must be a PEM-encoded value. This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1. If null, HTTPS connections with the upstream identity provider will rely on a default set of system trusted roots.
        Parameters:
        certificateAuthorityData - New value for the property.

      • setAdditionalScopes

        public ProvidersTypes.CreateSpec.Builder setAdditionalScopes(java.util.List<java.lang.String> additionalScopes)
        Additional scopes to be requested in tokens issued by this identity provider. This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1. If null, no additional scopes will be requested.
        Parameters:
        additionalScopes - New value for the property.

      • setAdditionalAuthorizeParameters

        public ProvidersTypes.CreateSpec.Builder setAdditionalAuthorizeParameters(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> additionalAuthorizeParameters)
        Any additional parameters to be sent to the upstream identity provider during the authorize request in the OAuth2 authorization code flow. One use case is to pass in a default tenant ID if you have a multi-tenant identity provider. For instance, with VMware's Cloud Services Platform, if your organization ID is 'long-form-org-id', the 'orgLink' parameter can be set to "/csp/gateway/am/api/orgs/long-form-org-id" to allow users logging in to leverage that organization. This property was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1. If null, no additional parameters will be sent to the upstream identity provider.
        Parameters:
        additionalAuthorizeParameters - New value for the property.
